PN,41101
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FA gold watch presented to the engineer
OL,8,Fof a steamship which rescued more than
OL,9,F700 passengers from the Titanic could
OL,10,Fmake #100,000 at auction in Kent.
OL,12,FJohn Richardson was the sixth engineer
OL,13,Faboard the RMS Carpathia, a Cunard
OL,14,FLine transatlantic passenger ship that
OL,15,Frescued survivors from the Titanic's
OL,16,Flifeboats.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FThe Carpathia, on its way from New
OL,8,FYork for Europe, changed course after
OL,9,Fthe ship's wireless operator picked up
OL,10,Fthe distress call "we've struck ice,
OL,11,Fcome at once".
OL,13,FIt set off at full speed and reached
OL,14,Fthe Titanic two hours after it had
OL,15,Fsunk in the North Atlantic on April
OL,16,F15, 1912, with the loss of 1,500 lives.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FThe 18-carat gold timepiece,
OL,8,Fhallmarked 1912, is engraved
OL,9,F"Presented to J. Richardson as a mark
OL,10,Fof appreciation for conspicuous
OL,11,Fservices rendered R.M.S. Titanic, 15th
OL,12,FApril 1912."
OL,26,@qD@AOUtD@LO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FJustin Matthews, director of Hansons
OL,8,FAuctioneers in Penshurst, where the
OL,9,Fwatch goes under the hammer on April
OL,10,F22, said: "When I first held it in my
OL,11,Fhand I had goose bumps ` it was spine
OL,12,Ftingling to know its connections to
OL,13,Fone of the most famous, and tragic,
OL,14,Fevents of the 20th century. It is an
OL,15,Fhonour to offer it for sale."
OL,26,@rD@KOUwD@]O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FRichardson, then aged 26, was one of
OL,8,Fseveral engineers honoured by the
OL,9,FLiverpool-based Carpathia Engineers'
OL,10,FPresentation Fund ` whose founders
OL,11,Fbelieved the vital role the below deck
OL,12,Fcrew played in the rescue had been
OL,13,Fwoefully overlooked.
OL,15,FThe engineers' neglect was, they said,
OL,16,F"a reproach which, in Liverpool at
OL,17,Fleast, had to be wiped out."
OL,26,@xD@AOUyD@\O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FOne of the biggest contributions came
OL,8,Ffrom Mrs John Jacob Astor, the widow
OL,9,Fof John Jacob Astor IV, one of the
OL,10,Fwealthiest men in the world, who died
OL,11,Fin the disaster.
OL,13,FHer donation of $200 (#6,000 in
OL,14,Ftoday's money) helped galvanise
OL,15,Finterest in the fund which counted
OL,16,FLiverpool's Lady Mayoress, the
OL,17,FCountess of Derby and municipal
OL,18,Fleaders among its supporters.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FJohn Richardson was one of three
OL,8,Fengineers, with the others at sea,
OL,9,Fpresented with the Hunter pocket watch
OL,10,Fat a ceremony on December 14, 1912, by
OL,11,Fthe Mayor of Liverpool.
OL,13,FFollowing the disaster a number of
OL,14,Ffundraising initiatives were set up by
OL,15,Fboth Titanic survivors and members of
OL,16,Fthe public, all keen to honour its
OL,17,Fheroes.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FSix weeks after the rescue the
OL,8,FCarpathia's Captain Arthur Rostron and
OL,9,Fthe crew were honoured in New York
OL,10,FCity with gold medals going to senior
OL,11,Fofficers, silver to junior officers
OL,12,Fand bronze to the crew.
OL,14,FA pocket watch Captain Rostron
OL,15,Freceived from Mrs John Jacob Astor
OL,16,Fsold at auction for a then record-
OL,17,Fbreaking #1.56m in 2024.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FJustin Matthews continued: "While the
OL,8,Fcaptain of the Carpathia took most of
OL,9,Fthe plaudits for the rescue of those
OL,10,F705 men, women and children adrift in
OL,11,Fthe Titanic's lifeboats, it was
OL,12,Fworkers in the engine room, like John
OL,13,FRichardson, who were high on the list
OL,14,Fof heroes.
OL,16,F"Their work wasn't visible to
OL,17,Fpassengers, or survivors, but without
OL,18,Fit, the rescue simply wouldn't have
OL,19,Fhappened."
OL,26,@oD@\OU{D@JO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FWhen Captain Rostron received
OL,8,FTitanic's distress call, he ordered
OL,9,Fmaximum speed meaning the engine room
OL,10,Fcrew had to keep multiple coal-fired
OL,11,Fboilers running at peak output with
OL,12,Fstokers shovelling coal in intense
OL,13,Fheat.
OL,15,FJustin Matthews said: "The engineers
OL,16,Fturned the Carpathia from a passenger
OL,17,Fship into a high-speed rescue vessel
OL,18,Funder emergency conditions.
OL,26,@wD@WOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,F"Their skill, endurance, and judgment
OL,8,Fdirectly translated into lives saved."
OL,9,FEven after the rescue, weary engineers
OL,10,Fhad to ensure the safe passage of
OL,11,F1,740 people back to New York.
OL,13,FRichardson, the son of a Scottish
OL,14,Fmaster mariner, was born in Carlisle
OL,15,Fon May 26, 1885.
OL,17,FBy 1901 the family had moved to
OL,18,FBirkenhead, with Richardson described
OL,19,Fas working as an apprentice mechanical
OL,20,Fengineer.
OL,26,@pD@fO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41112
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,FHis name first appears on crew lists
OL,8,Fin February 1907 when he was senior
OL,9,Ffourth engineer aboard the Campania.
OL,11,FBy the time of Carpathia rescue, he
OL,12,Fwas a married man and father of two.
OL,13,FAfter the fateful trip little is
OL,14,Fknown, in the 1930s the family moved
OL,15,Fto New York. The watch stayed in his
OL,16,Ffamily for almost a century before
OL,17,Ffirst being offered for sale in 2003.
OL,19,FJustin Matthews continued: "Collectors
OL,20,Fand the public's interest in the
OL,21,FTitanic shows no sign of diminishing.
OL,26,@{D@\OU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G12/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41113
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1776082266
OL,3,CWatch owned by an unsung hero of
OL,4,CTitanic rescue set to make #100,000 at
OL,5,Cauction
OL,7,F"In fact, on the contrary, even more
OL,8,Fthan a 114 years later, recent prices
OL,9,Fachieved at auction testify to our
OL,10,Fongoing fascination."
OL,12,FThe watch went on public display at
OL,13,FSouthampton Maritime Museum's
OL,14,Fexhibition to mark the 80th
OL,15,Fanniversary of the Titanic disaster.
OL,26,@rD@UO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G13/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
